goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?
goals.visualization: Box plot of life_expect by country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the median, quartiles, and outliers of life expectancy across different countries.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between fertility rate and population?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of pop vs fertility
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a positive or negative correlation between population and fertility rate.

goals.question: What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of life_expect by year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is an increasing or decreasing trend of life expectancy over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of population across different clusters?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the distribution of population across different clusters.

goals.question: What is the average life expectancy of each cluster?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of mean life_expect by cluster
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the average life expectancy of each cluster and compare them with each other.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='country', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='fertility', y='pop', hue='country', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between fertility rate and population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.legend(title='Country', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(title='Life Expectancy', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pop', hue='cluster', multiple='stack', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different clusters?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Cluster', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    mean_life_expect = data.groupby('cluster')['life_expect'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='life_expect', data=mean_life_expect, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the average life expectancy of each cluster?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Average Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(title='Clusters', loc='upper right', labels=mean_life_expect['cluster'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
